Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.18,0:00:04.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome to the program!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.09,0:00:08.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Our theme this month is \N“Organized to Do God’s Will.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.43,0:00:10.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Among other things, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.43,0:00:12.33,Default,,0,0,0,,we will look at how our young brothers \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.33,0:00:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,can be encouraged to reach out \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.40,0:00:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,so as to take the lead in the congregation. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.13,0:00:22.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You will also enjoy this report \Non the blessings around the world \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.51,0:00:24.94,Default,,0,0,0,,from using carts in our ministry, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.94,0:00:27.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and we’ll find out how \Nthe organization makes sure \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.98,0:00:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,our meeting places are properly utilized. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.32,0:00:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the July program \Nof JW Broadcasting!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.37,0:00:56.54,Default,,0,0,0,,There are people who believe \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.54,0:00:59.64,Default,,0,0,0,,there is no need \Nfor a religious organization. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.64,0:01:03.18,Default,,0,0,0,,They feel they have \Ntheir own personal relationship with God \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.18,0:01:05.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and that is good enough. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.32,0:01:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,They see no need to be associated \Nwith a specific organization. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.32,0:01:14.56,Default,,0,0,0,,However, what does \NGod’s own inspired Word suggest? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.56,0:01:18.09,Default,,0,0,0,,That he would use an organization, \Nor channel, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.09,0:01:20.73,Default,,0,0,0,,through which spiritual food \Nwould be dispensed \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.73,0:01:23.97,Default,,0,0,0,,from his Word, the Bible. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.97,0:01:27.70,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, \N1 Peter 2:17 says \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.70,0:01:31.71,Default,,0,0,0,,to “have love \Nfor the whole association of brothers.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.71,0:01:34.81,Default,,0,0,0,,One dictionary definition for “association” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.81,0:01:40.62,Default,,0,0,0,,is “an organization of persons \Nhaving a common interest.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.62,0:01:43.72,Default,,0,0,0,,We have a very interesting, insightful look \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.72,0:01:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,at the organization in the first century. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.72,0:01:51.66,Default,,0,0,0,,If we glance down through chapter 15 \Nof the book of Acts, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.66,0:01:53.90,Default,,0,0,0,,we can gain some insight. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.90,0:01:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Verse 1 indicates there was \Nan issue that caused a disagreement \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.07,0:02:00.94,Default,,0,0,0,,between some of the members \Nof the congregation. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.94,0:02:03.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Then verse 2 says: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.01,0:02:07.01,Default,,0,0,0,,“But after quite a bit \Nof dissension and disputing \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.01,0:02:09.45,Default,,0,0,0,,“by Paul and Barnabas with them, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.45,0:02:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,“it was arranged for Paul, \NBarnabas, and some of the others \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.48,0:02:16.65,Default,,0,0,0,,“to go up to the apostles \Nand elders in Jerusalem \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.65,0:02:19.29,Default,,0,0,0,,regarding this issue.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.29,0:02:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It sounds like an organization to me. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.16,0:02:24.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And after considerable discussion \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.69,0:02:27.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and with the help of God’s holy spirit, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.83,0:02:29.83,Default,,0,0,0,,what transpired? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.83,0:02:34.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Verses 22 and 23 say: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.04,0:02:38.68,Default,,0,0,0,,“Then the apostles and the elders, \Ntogether with the whole congregation, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.68,0:02:41.88,Default,,0,0,0,,“decided to send chosen men \Nfrom among them to Antioch, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.88,0:02:43.61,Default,,0,0,0,,“along with Paul and Barnabas; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.61,0:02:47.32,Default,,0,0,0,,“they sent Judas \Nwho was called Barsabbas and Silas, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.32,0:02:49.72,Default,,0,0,0,,“who were leading men \Namong the brothers. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.72,0:02:52.89,Default,,0,0,0,,They wrote this \Nand sent it through them.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.89,0:02:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Then in verses 23-29 \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.16,0:02:59.16,Default,,0,0,0,,is the letter of direction \Nthat was delivered to Antioch \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.16,0:03:01.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and other congregations as well. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.46,0:03:05.13,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, in verse 41, \Nit says Paul and Silas \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.13,0:03:09.64,Default,,0,0,0,,“went through Syria and Cilicia, \Nstrengthening the congregations.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.64,0:03:12.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Chapter 16, verse 5 says: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.51,0:03:16.65,Default,,0,0,0,,“Then, indeed, the congregations \Ncontinued to be made firm in the faith \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.65,0:03:20.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and to increase in number day by day.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.42,0:03:25.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So it was not a matter \Nof isolated Christians sitting at home \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.09,0:03:28.36,Default,,0,0,0,,claiming to have \Na personal relationship with God. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.36,0:03:31.46,Default,,0,0,0,,No, the work was organized, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.46,0:03:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and congregations \Nkept being added “day by day.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.07,0:03:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,That is very similar to what we see \Nin Jehovah’s organization today. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.40,0:03:44.27,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, the organization \Nof Jehovah’s Witnesses is patterned \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.27,0:03:47.58,Default,,0,0,0,,after the first-century \NChristian congregation \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.58,0:03:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,as set forth in the Scriptures. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.48,0:03:53.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I would like to remind \Nall of Jehovah’s Witnesses\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.35,0:03:56.92,Default,,0,0,0,,—whether already baptized \Nor working toward baptism—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.92,0:04:01.96,Default,,0,0,0,,of this book, \NOrganized to Do Jehovah’s Will. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.96,0:04:04.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It provides an overall view \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.19,0:04:06.83,Default,,0,0,0,,of how the Christian congregation \Nis organized \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.83,0:04:09.07,Default,,0,0,0,,for getting God’s work done. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.07,0:04:12.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The book also offers counsel and direction \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.60,0:04:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to help us maintain unity \Nwith our brothers worldwide. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.21,0:04:19.21,Default,,0,0,0,,New ones need to become familiar \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.21,0:04:21.31,Default,,0,0,0,,with the operation \Nof Jehovah’s organization \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.31,0:04:23.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and learn how they can have a share \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.55,0:04:25.55,Default,,0,0,0,,in the modern-day preaching work. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.55,0:04:29.39,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, \Nwhen a Bible student progresses \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.39,0:04:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and desires to join us in the ministry \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.59,0:04:33.72,Default,,0,0,0,,as an unbaptized publisher, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.72,0:04:37.09,Default,,0,0,0,,the elders direct him \Nto make a study of this book, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.09,0:04:41.13,Default,,0,0,0,,including the “Questions for Those \NDesiring to Get Baptized” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.13,0:04:43.23,Default,,0,0,0,,in the appendix. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.23,0:04:47.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Even for those of us \Nwho have been baptized many years, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.47,0:04:49.61,Default,,0,0,0,,it may be good to schedule the reading \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.61,0:04:51.87,Default,,0,0,0,,of one chapter of the book each week \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.87,0:04:55.85,Default,,0,0,0,,during our personal study \Nor family worship. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.85,0:04:58.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It contains general information \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.08,0:05:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,concerning the duties \Nof elders and ministerial servants, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.52,0:05:03.52,Default,,0,0,0,,judicial procedures, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.52,0:05:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and various other features \Nof congregation organization.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.92,0:05:12.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I would like to take a few minutes \Nand review some of the information \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.33,0:05:15.97,Default,,0,0,0,,in chapter 1 of the publication. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.97,0:05:18.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Though there are thousands of national \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.27,0:05:20.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and international organizations \Naround the world, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.77,0:05:22.77,Default,,0,0,0,,they are organized \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.77,0:05:25.98,Default,,0,0,0,,according to human viewpoints \Nand philosophies. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.98,0:05:28.98,Default,,0,0,0,,But our organization is different; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.98,0:05:31.75,Default,,0,0,0,,it is theocratic. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.75,0:05:36.62,Default,,0,0,0,,That means it is ruled by Jehovah \Nas Head over all. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.62,0:05:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Isaiah 33:22 says that he is our Judge, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.36,0:05:44.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Lawgiver, and King. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.39,0:05:46.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Many large organizations appoint \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.83,0:05:50.50,Default,,0,0,0,,a chief executive officer, or CEO. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.50,0:05:54.44,Default,,0,0,0,,He is the executive \Nwith the chief decision-making authority \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.44,0:05:57.17,Default,,0,0,0,,in a business or corporation. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.17,0:06:01.24,Default,,0,0,0,,In a similar way, \NJehovah has appointed his Son, Jesus, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.24,0:06:04.95,Default,,0,0,0,,to be the one \Nwith chief decision-making authority \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.95,0:06:07.95,Default,,0,0,0,,over the congregation of God. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.95,0:06:11.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Ephesians 1:22 \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.95,0:06:15.73,Default,,0,0,0,,is speaking of Jehovah’s actions \Nin connection with Jesus. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.73,0:06:17.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It says: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.73,0:06:21.33,Default,,0,0,0,,“He also subjected all things under his feet \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.33,0:06:24.13,Default,,0,0,0,,“and made him head over all things \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.13,0:06:27.80,Default,,0,0,0,,with regard to the congregation.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.80,0:06:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,We see the structure \Nof the organization taking shape. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.44,0:06:35.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah is the Universal Sovereign, \Nthe King, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.01,0:06:37.41,Default,,0,0,0,,directing the millions of angels \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.41,0:06:40.02,Default,,0,0,0,,making up his heavenly organization. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.02,0:06:42.02,Default,,0,0,0,,But when it comes to directing \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.02,0:06:45.59,Default,,0,0,0,,the visible earthly part \Nof God’s organization, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.59,0:06:48.83,Default,,0,0,0,,he has delegated \Nthat responsibility to Jesus, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.83,0:06:51.56,Default,,0,0,0,,the head of the congregation of God. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.56,0:06:54.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Chapter 2 of the Organized book \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.50,0:06:58.50,Default,,0,0,0,,explains this Scriptural position of Jesus.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.50,0:07:02.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And how does Jesus direct \Nthe organization here on earth? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.44,0:07:06.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Matthew 24:45 says \Nthat Jesus has appointed \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.61,0:07:09.25,Default,,0,0,0,,a “faithful and discreet slave” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.25,0:07:13.05,Default,,0,0,0,,to serve \Nspiritual “food at the proper time.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.05,0:07:14.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.65,0:07:16.92,Default,,0,0,0,,seven anointed men \Nmake up the faithful slave, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.92,0:07:20.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and collectively, \Nthey are known as the Governing Body. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.59,0:07:24.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And Jesus uses the holy spirit \Nto direct these men \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.03,0:07:27.56,Default,,0,0,0,,in harmony with the Scriptures. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.56,0:07:29.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The Scriptural basis \Nfor this layer of organization \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.90,0:07:33.57,Default,,0,0,0,,is set forth in chapter 3 of the book. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.57,0:07:35.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Chapter 4 is entitled \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.61,0:07:39.11,Default,,0,0,0,,“How the Congregation \NIs Organized and Governed.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.11,0:07:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The organizational structure \Nincorporates Branch Committees, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.28,0:07:48.05,Default,,0,0,0,,circuit overseers, elders, \Nand ministerial servants. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.05,0:07:50.45,Default,,0,0,0,,The subject index in the back of the book \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.45,0:07:54.56,Default,,0,0,0,,can be useful \Nto quickly gain access to information \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.56,0:07:58.06,Default,,0,0,0,,on various aspects of the organization.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.06,0:08:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Suppose you’re a young person, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.50,0:08:03.77,Default,,0,0,0,,maybe even \Na relatively young married couple. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.77,0:08:05.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The circuit overseer is visiting, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.90,0:08:08.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and he asks you \Nwhat spiritual goals you have. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.77,0:08:10.77,Default,,0,0,0,,How would you answer? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.77,0:08:12.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Would your mind start racing, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.78,0:08:17.81,Default,,0,0,0,,trying to think \Nof various avenues of service available? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.81,0:08:22.65,Default,,0,0,0,,How about now, \Nbefore you are asked such a question, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.65,0:08:26.82,Default,,0,0,0,,you look in the subject index \Nunder “Goals”? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.82,0:08:31.83,Default,,0,0,0,,There are 11 references \Nto paragraphs in the book on that subject. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.83,0:08:34.03,Default,,0,0,0,,After reading about all \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.03,0:08:36.53,Default,,0,0,0,,of the possibilities \Nand different categories, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.53,0:08:39.64,Default,,0,0,0,,you would be \Nin a better position to plan your life \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.64,0:08:41.64,Default,,0,0,0,,for a great future \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.64,0:08:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,in the earthly part \Nof Jehovah’s organization.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.04,0:08:48.04,Default,,0,0,0,,At this time, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.04,0:08:51.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I would like to draw your attention \Nto a very important factor \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.85,0:08:54.22,Default,,0,0,0,,in a new one’s making progress \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.22,0:08:57.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and attaining spiritual stability. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.35,0:09:02.02,Default,,0,0,0,,On page 213 of the Organized book, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.02,0:09:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,it discusses a person \Ninterested in being baptized. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.56,0:09:09.80,Default,,0,0,0,,After the elders go over the questions \Nin part 3 of the book, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.80,0:09:11.80,Default,,0,0,0,,it says this: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.80,0:09:16.54,Default,,0,0,0,,“If he has not completed his study \Nof the Bible Teach and ‘God’s Love’ books, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.54,0:09:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the elders should make arrangements \Nfor someone to help him do so.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.88,0:09:27.62,Default,,0,0,0,,The two books \Ncomplement each other so well. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.62,0:09:31.95,Default,,0,0,0,,When someone becomes a dedicated \Nand baptized servant of Jehovah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.95,0:09:36.06,Default,,0,0,0,,we want them to stay \Nclosely attached to the organization. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.06,0:09:38.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet every year, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.06,0:09:40.70,Default,,0,0,0,,there are a number \Nwho stop attending meetings \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.70,0:09:42.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and become inactive. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.70,0:09:44.70,Default,,0,0,0,,At times, \Nit has been found \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.70,0:09:48.30,Default,,0,0,0,,that they did not finish \Nstudying the two books.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.30,0:09:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.64,0:09:51.97,Default,,0,0,0,,the Bible Teach book helps new ones \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.97,0:09:54.54,Default,,0,0,0,,to have an accurate knowledge of the Bible, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.54,0:09:57.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and they often learn to love Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.81,0:09:59.85,Default,,0,0,0,,The “Keep Yourselves in God’s Love” book \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.85,0:10:02.79,Default,,0,0,0,,helps us to learn to apply the Bible \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.79,0:10:05.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and live in harmony \Nwith Jehovah’s standards. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.86,0:10:09.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Notice what Jesus told his faithful apostles \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.86,0:10:15.93,Default,,0,0,0,,at John 15:10: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.93,0:10:19.80,Default,,0,0,0,,“If you observe my commandments, \Nyou will remain in my love, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.80,0:10:22.91,Default,,0,0,0,,“just as I have observed \Nthe commandments of the Father \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.91,0:10:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and remain in his love.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.58,0:10:29.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you notice \Nthat Jesus remained in God’s love \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.61,0:10:32.68,Default,,0,0,0,,by observing his Father’s commandments? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.68,0:10:35.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The same is true of us today. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.25,0:10:37.62,Default,,0,0,0,,To remain in God’s love, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.62,0:10:41.19,Default,,0,0,0,,we need to apply the truth \Nin our everyday life. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.19,0:10:45.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And what is the result \Nif we keep ourselves in God’s love? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.39,0:10:48.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It is so clearly stated \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.06,0:10:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,in Jude 21: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.60,0:10:55.10,Default,,0,0,0,,“In order to keep yourselves in God’s love, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.10,0:10:58.37,Default,,0,0,0,,“while you await the mercy \Nof our Lord Jesus Christ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.37,0:11:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,with everlasting life in view.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.14,0:11:07.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Staying in God’s love \Nresults in everlasting life.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.15,0:11:10.45,Default,,0,0,0,,It is so important \Nto make sure our Bible students \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.45,0:11:13.86,Default,,0,0,0,,complete a study of both books, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.86,0:11:16.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and that applies to our children too. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.36,0:11:18.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes as parents, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.46,0:11:20.73,Default,,0,0,0,,we can assume \Nthat our children are developing \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.73,0:11:23.37,Default,,0,0,0,,a trusting relationship with Jehovah \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.37,0:11:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,because they have been going \Nto meetings since they were very small. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.20,0:11:32.21,Default,,0,0,0,,A relationship with Jehovah \Ndoes not happen by means of osmosis. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.21,0:11:36.31,Default,,0,0,0,,A child does not simply absorb \Nand assimilate truth \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.31,0:11:38.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and a love for God \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.31,0:11:40.55,Default,,0,0,0,,just by being in the presence of others \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.55,0:11:44.32,Default,,0,0,0,,who have a close relationship with Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.32,0:11:48.19,Default,,0,0,0,,We very much appreciate \Nall of the videos we have, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.19,0:11:52.13,Default,,0,0,0,,including Become Jehovah’s Friend \Nand JW Broadcasting. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.13,0:11:55.70,Default,,0,0,0,,But new ones and young ones \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.70,0:12:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,need to be able to go \Nthrough the process of deep study \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.07,0:12:02.17,Default,,0,0,0,,to get to the Bible’s truth \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.17,0:12:04.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and get it etched into their minds \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.17,0:12:06.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and lodged deep in their hearts. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.94,0:12:08.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.94,0:12:11.75,Default,,0,0,0,,if you parents realize \Nthat you have not studied \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.75,0:12:14.12,Default,,0,0,0,,both books with your young ones, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.12,0:12:19.16,Default,,0,0,0,,it would be good to see \Nthat a schedule is established to do so.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.16,0:12:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The Governing Body gives all credit \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.16,0:12:25.49,Default,,0,0,0,,for the success \Nof this organization to Jehovah \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.49,0:12:29.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and the appointed head \Nof the congregation, Jesus Christ. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.50,0:12:32.13,Default,,0,0,0,,We are just imperfect men trying to follow \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.13,0:12:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the lead of Christ and the holy spirit. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.80,0:12:39.81,Default,,0,0,0,,At 1 Corinthians 1:26, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.81,0:12:41.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Paul says:\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.94,0:12:44.21,Default,,0,0,0,,“For you see his calling of you, brothers,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.21,0:12:47.75,Default,,0,0,0,,that there are not many wise \Nin a fleshly way.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.75,0:12:49.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Verse 27 says: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.75,0:12:52.82,Default,,0,0,0,,“But God chose \Nthe foolish things of the world \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.82,0:12:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,to put the wise men to shame.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.96,0:12:58.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Then verse 30 says that Christ Jesus \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.29,0:13:02.80,Default,,0,0,0,,“has become to us wisdom from God.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.80,0:13:05.57,Default,,0,0,0,,That is where the direction and wisdom \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.57,0:13:07.67,Default,,0,0,0,,of the organization come from, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.67,0:13:10.91,Default,,0,0,0,,not from mere man. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.91,0:13:14.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The words of Jehovah \Nto the prophet Zechariah fit today \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.84,0:13:18.65,Default,,0,0,0,,when we see \Nthe amazing advances in the organization. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.65,0:13:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Zechariah 4:6 says: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.72,0:13:23.79,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Not by a military force, nor by power, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.79,0:13:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,but by my spirit,’ says Jehovah of armies.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.19,0:13:32.19,Default,,0,0,0,,While there are \Nsome well-educated and prominent men \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.19,0:13:36.20,Default,,0,0,0,,who have accepted the truth \Nand are now our fellow brothers, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.20,0:13:40.64,Default,,0,0,0,,the majority in the organization \Ncome from a more humble background. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.64,0:13:42.64,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.64,0:13:45.07,Default,,0,0,0,,among the first \Nof Jehovah’s modern-day servants \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.07,0:13:48.11,Default,,0,0,0,,to introduce the Kingdom message \Nto people in Denmark \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.11,0:13:50.11,Default,,0,0,0,,was a shoemaker. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.11,0:13:53.35,Default,,0,0,0,,In Switzerland and France, \Nit was a gardener. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.35,0:13:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,In many parts of Africa, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.35,0:13:58.22,Default,,0,0,0,,the message was carried \Nby itinerant workers. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.22,0:14:01.46,Default,,0,0,0,,In Brazil, sailors had a share. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.46,0:14:05.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Quite a few of the Polish Witnesses \Nin northern France \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.13,0:14:07.40,Default,,0,0,0,,were coal miners. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.40,0:14:10.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah and Jesus use all of us \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.37,0:14:13.24,Default,,0,0,0,,to get a remarkable work accomplished. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.24,0:14:17.77,Default,,0,0,0,,We are proud to be a part \Nof this spirit-directed organization. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.77,0:14:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,As one older circuit overseer \Nwas heard to say, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.88,0:14:25.88,Default,,0,0,0,,“This is the best imperfect organization \Non earth!” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.88,0:14:29.62,Default,,0,0,0,,There are no perfect organizations on earth. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.62,0:14:33.49,Default,,0,0,0,,However, this is the best of them all. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.49,0:14:36.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And we appreciate \Nthe contribution all of you make \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.93,0:14:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to the success \Nof the preaching work worldwide.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.16,0:14:44.63,Default,,0,0,0,,With that contribution in mind, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.63,0:14:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,consider for a moment \Nthe huge load elders carry \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.40,0:14:50.31,Default,,0,0,0,,in caring for our congregations. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.31,0:14:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Some of them are now advanced in age. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.98,0:14:55.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So how can young brothers be trained \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.58,0:14:58.61,Default,,0,0,0,,to qualify for increased responsibilities? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.61,0:15:00.85,Default,,0,0,0,,In this dramatization, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.85,0:15:03.72,Default,,0,0,0,,a congregation faces a change \Non its elder body \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.72,0:15:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that brought that question to the fore.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.77,0:15:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re very happy for Daniel. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.50,0:15:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,He’s going to be a blessing \Nin his new assignment. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.98,0:15:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,But we are going to miss him \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.98,0:15:34.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and everything he was doing \Nfor the congregation. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.98,0:15:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,This will change things for us.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.46,0:15:48.86,Default,,0,0,0,,We really want to be there \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.86,0:15:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,for our brothers and sisters.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.20,0:16:22.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And it’s true: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.21,0:16:26.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Having plenty to do \Nin the Lord’s work is good. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.10,0:16:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But where will we get more help?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.05,0:16:39.05,Default,,0,0,0,,We do have good ministerial servants \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.05,0:16:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,like Richie. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.76,0:16:51.53,Default,,0,0,0,,But after Daniel left, \Nour elder body is one fewer now. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.53,0:16:54.26,Default,,0,0,0,,That prompted a good question: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.26,0:16:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Are we doing all we can \Nto train our brothers?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.37,0:17:07.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Richie, do you have some time for me? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.71,0:17:09.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I have some calls you can help me with.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.78,0:17:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure, I’d like that.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.92,0:17:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I realized it had been \Na while since we talked \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.16,0:17:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,about him qualifying to do more. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.16,0:17:24.99,Default,,0,0,0,,He explained that he wanted to help \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.99,0:17:27.06,Default,,0,0,0,,but didn’t want to appear presumptuous. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.06,0:17:29.06,Default,,0,0,0,,He’d been praying about it, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.06,0:17:32.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and he wanted to know what else \Nhe could do to keep reaching out.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.90,0:17:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Talking to Richie \Nmade me think of Jesus’ example. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.01,0:17:42.64,Default,,0,0,0,,His disciples offered themselves willingly, \Nand he trained them. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.64,0:17:45.75,Default,,0,0,0,,They were eager but needed his direction. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.75,0:17:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus’ training gave them confidence \Nto do the assignments he gave them. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.65,0:17:54.99,Default,,0,0,0,,They were happy, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.99,0:17:56.99,Default,,0,0,0,,not just to follow Jesus, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.99,0:17:59.83,Default,,0,0,0,,but to work alongside him. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.83,0:18:03.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And Jesus was happy to share his work.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.47,0:18:05.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Up to his final evening with them, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.83,0:18:07.94,Default,,0,0,0,,he prepared them for the work ahead. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.94,0:18:10.87,Default,,0,0,0,,“Most truly I say to you, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.87,0:18:15.38,Default,,0,0,0,,“whoever exercises faith in me \Nwill also do the works that I do; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.38,0:18:17.48,Default,,0,0,0,,“and he will do works greater than these, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.48,0:18:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,because I am going my way to the Father.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.39,0:18:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I now remember how much training \NI had received from the brothers.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.50,0:18:38.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It was easy to forget \Nthat I didn’t always get \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.70,0:18:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,things right at first. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.71,0:18:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Soon, \NRichie was taking on more responsibility. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.48,0:18:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And he told me something \Nthat I too once felt. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.15,0:19:01.39,Default,,0,0,0,,He just didn’t realize how much work \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.39,0:19:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,went into caring for Jehovah’s sheep. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.73,0:19:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But once he knew, \Nhe was glad he offered himself willingly.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.94,0:19:25.15,Default,,0,0,0,,We commend all our hard-working elders \Nfor their fine work \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.15,0:19:27.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and also those of you who support them, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.95,0:19:32.15,Default,,0,0,0,,whether you are a ministerial servant \Nor perhaps the wife of an elder. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.15,0:19:34.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Without your help and support, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.22,0:19:37.03,Default,,0,0,0,,it would be very difficult \Nfor our dear elders\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.03,0:19:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,to carry out their weighty responsibilities.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.16,0:19:44.03,Default,,0,0,0,,While there is a lot of work \Nto be done on a local level, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.03,0:19:47.27,Default,,0,0,0,,there is an unprecedented global effort \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.27,0:19:50.54,Default,,0,0,0,,to provide spiritual food \Nto all of God’s people. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.54,0:19:52.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Under the direction \Nof the Teaching Committee \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.54,0:19:54.54,Default,,0,0,0,,of the Governing Body, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.54,0:19:57.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the Audio/Video Services Department, \Nor AVS, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.88,0:20:02.65,Default,,0,0,0,,takes the lead in producing \Naudio and video publications.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.65,0:20:05.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s been said that if a picture \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.05,0:20:07.22,Default,,0,0,0,,is worth a thousand words, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.22,0:20:10.23,Default,,0,0,0,,then a video is worth a million! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.23,0:20:13.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Videos stir our emotions, don’t they? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.30,0:20:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And they can be \Nvery powerful teaching tools. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.40,0:20:19.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Russell recognized this fact. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.10,0:20:22.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Back in 1914, \Nthe small group of Bible Students \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.70,0:20:25.64,Default,,0,0,0,,presented the “Photo-Drama of Creation” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.64,0:20:29.65,Default,,0,0,0,,to over nine million people worldwide, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.65,0:20:32.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and the response was overwhelming. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.05,0:20:35.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It was clear that Jehovah \Nblessed their efforts \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.38,0:20:40.39,Default,,0,0,0,,at spreading the Bible’s message \Nin a visual way. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.39,0:20:43.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, over a hundred years later, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.23,0:20:46.73,Default,,0,0,0,,“the faithful and discreet slave” \Nis producing videos.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.73,0:20:49.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And for many years, basically, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.10,0:20:52.70,Default,,0,0,0,,one large public-release video \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.70,0:20:56.31,Default,,0,0,0,,was being released, \Nor produced, each year. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.31,0:20:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, back in 2011, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.44,0:21:03.51,Default,,0,0,0,,the video Faith in Action, Part 2 \Nwas released. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.51,0:21:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And it required a tremendous effort \Nto produce the video master, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.98,0:21:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,the audio tracks, the graphics, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.72,0:21:15.72,Default,,0,0,0,,the music, the on-screen text \Nfor one video.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.72,0:21:19.03,Default,,0,0,0,,However, just five years later, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.03,0:21:21.33,Default,,0,0,0,,the work has grown from producing \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.33,0:21:24.23,Default,,0,0,0,,an average of one video per year \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.23,0:21:27.94,Default,,0,0,0,,to one video per day. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.94,0:21:32.94,Default,,0,0,0,,This is because videos are now \Na regular part of our website, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.94,0:21:36.68,Default,,0,0,0,,the broadcasts, \Nour ministry, the conventions, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.68,0:21:39.35,Default,,0,0,0,,meetings, and other special events. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.35,0:21:41.45,Default,,0,0,0,,In 2016, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.45,0:21:45.39,Default,,0,0,0,,more than 350 videos were produced. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.39,0:21:48.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Under the direction \Nof the Teaching Committee, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.09,0:21:51.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Audio/Video Services (AVS) \Nhas been entrusted with this work.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.89,0:21:56.47,Default,,0,0,0,,But with this rapid increase \Nin the amount of videos produced, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.47,0:21:59.30,Default,,0,0,0,,how is all this accomplished? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.30,0:22:01.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps you’ve heard the expression \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.47,0:22:03.67,Default,,0,0,0,,“it takes a village.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.67,0:22:07.38,Default,,0,0,0,,In this case, \Nit takes an entire globe. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.38,0:22:10.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Please enjoy the following video \Nfor a close-up look \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.81,0:22:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,at how audio and video work \Nis accomplished worldwide.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.49,0:22:27.83,Default,,0,0,0,,To assist with the growing workload \Nin Audio/Video Services, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.83,0:22:29.83,Default,,0,0,0,,the Governing Body has approved \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.83,0:22:32.83,Default,,0,0,0,,11 full-time Regional Video Teams (RVT) \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.83,0:22:34.94,Default,,0,0,0,,in branches around the world.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.94,0:22:36.94,Default,,0,0,0,,But it doesn’t stop there. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.94,0:22:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Bethelites, commuters, \Nand remote workers in many other branches \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.88,0:22:43.98,Default,,0,0,0,,also provide valuable assistance.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.98,0:22:46.28,Default,,0,0,0,,How do we work with all these teams? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.28,0:22:49.72,Default,,0,0,0,,After receiving direction \Nfrom the Governing Body committees \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.72,0:22:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,for upcoming videos, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.82,0:22:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,AVS then assigns \Neach video to a capable team.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.99,0:23:00.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Once the team accepts the assignment, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.43,0:23:03.27,Default,,0,0,0,,we provide them \Nwith the necessary direction \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.27,0:23:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,as well as answer \Nany questions they may have. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.04,0:23:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Then the team goes to work.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.99,0:23:28.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of being a small group, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.16,0:23:32.53,Default,,0,0,0,,each team member may have to wear \Nmultiple hats to get the job done.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.53,0:23:36.33,Default,,0,0,0,,From start to finish, \Nthey all work very hard \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.33,0:23:38.57,Default,,0,0,0,,to deliver a completed, edited video \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.57,0:23:41.57,Default,,0,0,0,,to us by the designated time. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.57,0:23:45.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Later, you may see these videos \Non JW Broadcasting, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.54,0:23:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,jw.org, or other places. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.48,0:23:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you like to meet \Nsome of our RVT family?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.39,0:24:05.93,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s a privilege. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.93,0:24:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We meet friends who have suffered \Nsome hardships and trials, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.93,0:24:13.20,Default,,0,0,0,,but because of their trust in Jehovah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.20,0:24:15.20,Default,,0,0,0,,they were able to overcome them, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.20,0:24:18.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and we see the results of their loyalty. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.41,0:24:21.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it strengthens our determination \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.58,0:24:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to also stay loyal.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.48,0:24:28.72,Default,,0,0,0,,We are a joyful team \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.72,0:24:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,with a lot of humor, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.15,0:24:32.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and we work together very harmoniously. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.75,0:24:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You could say that we \Nare like a little family. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.52,0:24:38.93,Default,,0,0,0,,We look forward to the next day \Nwhen we go to work again. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.93,0:24:41.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s unbelievable how many dear brothers \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.23,0:24:44.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and sisters we’ve gotten to know \Nthrough these projects. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.73,0:24:46.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Close ties can develop, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.54,0:24:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and it is not uncommon \Nthat tears flow when the project is over \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.67,0:24:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and it is time to say good-bye.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.68,0:24:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes we would film \Non private or state property, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.11,0:25:01.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and I would have to approach the manager \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.28,0:25:03.49,Default,,0,0,0,,and let them know \Nwhat we were planning to shoot \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.49,0:25:05.49,Default,,0,0,0,,at the location. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.49,0:25:10.83,Default,,0,0,0,,This wasn’t easy for me \Nbecause I’m not very good with words. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.83,0:25:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And many people in Korea tend to have \Na biased view of Jehovah’s Witnesses, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.80,0:25:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,so this made it even harder for me. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.60,0:25:21.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So I prayed to Jehovah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.77,0:25:25.31,Default,,0,0,0,,asking for his guidance and wisdom. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.31,0:25:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I was surprised to find that many \Nwere more than willing to help us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.61,0:25:35.95,Default,,0,0,0,,These experiences help me to realize \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.95,0:25:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jehovah always answers \Nour prayers for strength and courage.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.79,0:25:46.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to balance your time around work, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.13,0:25:49.63,Default,,0,0,0,,around being the head of a family, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.63,0:25:51.73,Default,,0,0,0,,being an elder, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.73,0:25:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,or other responsibilities \Nthat you have in the congregation. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.00,0:25:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s when you really see Jehovah’s hand\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.07,0:26:02.51,Default,,0,0,0,,—when you see the mountain of challenge, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.51,0:26:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,but you overcome it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.98,0:26:05.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And you know it wasn’t you. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.08,0:26:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It was impossible for you to do it yourself. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.02,0:26:12.92,Default,,0,0,0,,When I put even half \Nthe amount of energy and effort \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.92,0:26:16.93,Default,,0,0,0,,that I do into working for Jehovah \Ninto something secular, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.93,0:26:19.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m wiped out; I need a vacation. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.39,0:26:22.86,Default,,0,0,0,,But the more \NI put into working for Jehovah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.86,0:26:25.33,Default,,0,0,0,,the more I want to work. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.33,0:26:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,To know that you \Nare offering your skills to Jehovah\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.64,0:26:31.17,Default,,0,0,0,,—that is a blessing. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.17,0:26:34.34,Default,,0,0,0,,But, really, the blessing is seeing \Nyour relationship with Jehovah \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.34,0:26:36.78,Default,,0,0,0,,thrive and become stronger, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.78,0:26:40.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and you can see \Nthat he does keep his promises \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.05,0:26:45.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and that he supports you \Nmore than you’re supporting him.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.42,0:26:49.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Many of us aren’t able \Nto be full-time Bethelites, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.19,0:26:51.19,Default,,0,0,0,,but commuting really helps us \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.19,0:26:53.60,Default,,0,0,0,,get that small snippet of what it’s like \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.60,0:26:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to be a Bethelite \Nand realize what a privilege it is. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.17,0:27:00.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you’ve got a specific talent, use it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.84,0:27:03.57,Default,,0,0,0,,One day in Paradise, \Nsomeone is going to come to you \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.57,0:27:05.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and say, \N“How did you use your talent?” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.57,0:27:07.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe you’re a brilliant artist, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.31,0:27:09.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and you’re going \Nto proudly turn around and say: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.88,0:27:11.98,Default,,0,0,0,,“You know what? \NI used it for Jehovah.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.98,0:27:15.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if you’re young, \Nyou can learn skills \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.58,0:27:19.45,Default,,0,0,0,,and you can really assist \NJehovah’s organization \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.45,0:27:22.06,Default,,0,0,0,,now and in the future. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.06,0:27:26.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And there is no better boss \Nto work for than Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.13,0:27:29.43,Default,,0,0,0,,My advice to young ones: Go for it!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.43,0:27:32.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And during this past year, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.30,0:27:36.24,Default,,0,0,0,,we were excited to add \Na new team to our AVS family\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.24,0:27:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,—located in Mira Loma, California. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.98,0:27:44.78,Default,,0,0,0,,All in this group \Nhave made themselves available \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.78,0:27:47.95,Default,,0,0,0,,for video needs out there.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.95,0:27:50.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re able to take a person— \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.25,0:27:52.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re able to take an individual \Nthat has dedicated their life to Jehovah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.85,0:27:54.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and maybe they \Ndidn’t know at the time \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.09,0:27:55.59,Default,,0,0,0,,that they were going \Nto inspire somebody else \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.59,0:27:56.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and have somebody \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.59,0:27:58.93,Default,,0,0,0,,somewhere across the planet say: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.93,0:28:00.93,Default,,0,0,0,,“Wow! That’s exactly my life too. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.93,0:28:03.47,Default,,0,0,0,,“I’m so glad that this person \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.47,0:28:05.97,Default,,0,0,0,,“was selected to be on here \Nbecause that’s my life. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.97,0:28:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And that has triggered me \Nto want to do more for Jehovah.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.31,0:28:14.31,Default,,0,0,0,,You know it’s Jehovah’s holy spirit; \Nhe’s putting together a team; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.31,0:28:16.31,Default,,0,0,0,,he’s the Great Producer. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.31,0:28:18.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And what he really wants \Nis he wants people who have the talent, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.95,0:28:20.95,Default,,0,0,0,,but he wants people \Nwho have the holy spirit more \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.95,0:28:22.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and are willing to work for it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.95,0:28:27.06,Default,,0,0,0,,But he gives you the ability, \Nlike Oholiab and Bezalel, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.06,0:28:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,to be able to put your talents \Nthat you’ve learned to work for him.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.56,0:28:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,As you can see, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.56,0:28:36.90,Default,,0,0,0,,we’re part of a beautiful, \Nhardworking global team. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.90,0:28:41.27,Default,,0,0,0,,With so many hands helping the load \Nin so many time zones, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.27,0:28:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,we’re literally working on videos 24/7. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.18,0:28:51.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s a great privilege \Nto work alongside our extended family. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.08,0:28:53.05,Default,,0,0,0,,We learn from each other. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.05,0:28:55.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Their willing spirit, humble attitude, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.98,0:28:58.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and contagious joy \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.05,0:29:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,inspire all of us here in AVS.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.32,0:29:08.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Additionally, we receive \Nincredible support right at home too. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.20,0:29:10.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Virtually every department at Bethel \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.67,0:29:13.50,Default,,0,0,0,,supports the audio/video work in some way, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.50,0:29:18.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and we are very, very thankful. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.37,0:29:22.94,Default,,0,0,0,,With everyone’s help, \Nthe Bible’s message is being spread visually \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.94,0:29:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,throughout the earth \Nat unprecedented levels.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.19,0:29:33.56,Default,,0,0,0,,But how is any of this possible? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.56,0:29:35.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Russell said it best: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.89,0:29:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,‘This is not man’s work. It’s God’s.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.83,0:29:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah is certainly at the helm. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.00,0:29:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,As he foretold at Haggai 2:7: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.00,0:29:50.14,Default,,0,0,0,,“I will shake all the nations, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.14,0:29:53.41,Default,,0,0,0,,“and the precious things \Nof all the nations will come in; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.41,0:29:57.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and I will fill this house with glory.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.48,0:29:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,There is certainly \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.48,0:30:01.75,Default,,0,0,0,,a great shaking taking place \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.75,0:30:03.75,Default,,0,0,0,,worldwide. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.75,0:30:07.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And many of these precious ones \Nare offering themselves willingly \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.62,0:30:11.63,Default,,0,0,0,,to help Audio/Video Services \Naccomplish this great work, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.63,0:30:13.73,Default,,0,0,0,,thanks to Jehovah God, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.73,0:30:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,our Grand and Visual Instructor.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.83,0:30:23.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Our videos are a fantastic provision \Nfrom Jehovah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.81,0:30:26.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and what a teaching tool they have become. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.61,0:30:28.98,Default,,0,0,0,,We get many letters of appreciation \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.98,0:30:32.11,Default,,0,0,0,,about the use of our videos \Nin our midweek meetings. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.11,0:30:34.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And I agree; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.12,0:30:37.42,Default,,0,0,0,,the videos make the meetings \Nso much more dynamic. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.42,0:30:40.89,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, the week of July 17, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.89,0:30:44.73,Default,,0,0,0,,we will be considering the part\N “Do You Forgive Yourself?” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.73,0:30:47.50,Default,,0,0,0,,which includes a video that we first saw \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.50,0:30:50.30,Default,,0,0,0,,at the 2016 Regional Convention. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.30,0:30:54.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Make it a habit to prepare \Nfor these video considerations\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.44,0:30:57.57,Default,,0,0,0,, just as thoroughly \Nas you would any other part. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.57,0:31:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Your well-prepared comments \Nwill benefit the whole congregation.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.01,0:31:05.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And when we arrive \Nat the Kingdom Hall for a meeting, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.95,0:31:08.45,Default,,0,0,0,,don’t you agree \Nthat we all feel refreshed \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.45,0:31:12.95,Default,,0,0,0,,the moment we see the smiling faces \Nof our brothers and sisters? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.95,0:31:15.06,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s how I feel. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.06,0:31:19.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes we can even take \Nour beautiful meeting location for granted. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.73,0:31:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,But did you know \Nthat a lot of work goes into making sure \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.20,0:31:26.57,Default,,0,0,0,,that our Kingdom Halls are well utilized? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.57,0:31:30.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The Worldwide Design/Construction \NDepartment, or WDC, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.77,0:31:33.74,Default,,0,0,0,,is tasked with analyzing \Nour worldwide needs \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.74,0:31:37.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and providing direction \Nto Local Design/Construction Departments \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.68,0:31:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,on how best to use \Nour dedicated funds.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.45,0:31:48.42,Default,,0,0,0,,As we approach the end \Nof the present system of things, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.42,0:31:51.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah continues to speed up the work. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.26,0:31:55.26,Default,,0,0,0,,We now have \Nmore than 62,000 Kingdom Halls worldwide, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.26,0:31:57.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and the demand is still growing. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.43,0:32:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah’s blessing \Non the Kingdom work is undeniable, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.30,0:32:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,as this could not \Nhave been accomplished otherwise.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.01,0:32:07.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Many have been working for years \Nin support of Kingdom Hall \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.21,0:32:10.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and Assembly Hall construction projects, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.21,0:32:13.21,Default,,0,0,0,,most recently as part \Nof the Local Design/Construction, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.21,0:32:16.22,Default,,0,0,0,,or LDC, program. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.22,0:32:20.92,Default,,0,0,0,,This program was implemented \Nduring the 2014 service year \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.92,0:32:25.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and unifies the approach \Nfor construction of Kingdom Halls worldwide.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.66,0:32:28.33,Default,,0,0,0,,What has been accomplished \Nsince the program started? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.33,0:32:30.87,Default,,0,0,0,,At the end of the 2000 service year, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.87,0:32:34.67,Default,,0,0,0,,half of the publishers worldwide \Nmet in suitable meeting places. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.67,0:32:37.01,Default,,0,0,0,,However, the other half\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.01,0:32:39.41,Default,,0,0,0,,—approximately three million publishers—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.41,0:32:41.51,Default,,0,0,0,,met in places that were overcrowded \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.51,0:32:44.05,Default,,0,0,0,,or otherwise unsuitable as Kingdom Halls.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.05,0:32:46.05,Default,,0,0,0,,At that time, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.05,0:32:49.25,Default,,0,0,0,,27,000 Kingdom Halls were needed. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.25,0:32:52.39,Default,,0,0,0,,By 2014, \Nthe number of publishers meeting \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.39,0:32:55.66,Default,,0,0,0,,in unsuitable facilities had been reduced. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.66,0:32:58.26,Default,,0,0,0,,But because of growth in the organization, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.26,0:33:01.63,Default,,0,0,0,,this still meant that 1.6 million publishers \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.63,0:33:04.23,Default,,0,0,0,,did not have a suitable meeting place.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.23,0:33:06.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Since 2014, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.17,0:33:08.17,Default,,0,0,0,,that figure has been reduced \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.17,0:33:10.54,Default,,0,0,0,,by 25 percent. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.54,0:33:13.64,Default,,0,0,0,,What accounts for this significant reduction \Nin the backlog, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.64,0:33:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,allowing us to catch up faster \Nthan in the past? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.08,0:33:19.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Part of the answer \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.08,0:33:23.48,Default,,0,0,0,,lies in making efficient use \Nof the facilities we already have. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.48,0:33:25.55,Default,,0,0,0,,When providing food for thousands, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.55,0:33:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus made it clear \Nthat nothing should be wasted. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.96,0:33:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The LDC program applies that principle \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.86,0:33:33.90,Default,,0,0,0,,to the seats in our Kingdom Halls.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.90,0:33:35.90,Default,,0,0,0,,As noted earlier, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.90,0:33:39.10,Default,,0,0,0,,we have 62,000 Kingdom Halls worldwide. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.10,0:33:41.54,Default,,0,0,0,,On average, \Nonly 60 percent of the seats \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.54,0:33:43.84,Default,,0,0,0,,are filled for congregation meetings. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.84,0:33:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,That means that approximately three \Nto four million seats are empty \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.48,0:33:51.55,Default,,0,0,0,,during congregation meetings each week. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.55,0:33:55.65,Default,,0,0,0,,There are a number of options \Nto help make better use of these seats, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.65,0:33:58.85,Default,,0,0,0,,which will make the use \Nof each Kingdom Hall more efficient.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.85,0:34:00.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Consider, for example, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.66,0:34:02.89,Default,,0,0,0,,a Kingdom Hall in an urban area. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.89,0:34:04.89,Default,,0,0,0,,It has 200 seats \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.89,0:34:08.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and is used \Nby four congregations sharing the facility. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.30,0:34:10.83,Default,,0,0,0,,That means the Kingdom Hall will be in use \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.83,0:34:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,for four weeknight meetings \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.00,0:34:15.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and four weekend meetings.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.24,0:34:17.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It would definitely appear \Nto be fully utilized \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.71,0:34:19.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and suggests the need \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.71,0:34:22.18,Default,,0,0,0,,for new construction for further growth. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.18,0:34:25.45,Default,,0,0,0,,However, \Nhow many seats were in the Kingdom Hall? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.45,0:34:27.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Two hundred. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.45,0:34:30.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Multiplied by meetings \Nfor the four congregations, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.52,0:34:33.12,Default,,0,0,0,,this facility has a total seating capacity \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.12,0:34:35.29,Default,,0,0,0,,of 800 people. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.29,0:34:38.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Global records indicate that congregations \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.03,0:34:39.83,Default,,0,0,0,,using this size Kingdom Hall \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.83,0:34:41.30,Default,,0,0,0,,have an average attendance \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.30,0:34:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,of 120 at their meeting. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.00,0:34:47.90,Default,,0,0,0,,This could mean \Nthat only 480 seats are used \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.90,0:34:50.47,Default,,0,0,0,,by the four congregations \Nin this Kingdom Hall \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.47,0:34:53.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and 320 seats remain empty\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.61,0:34:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,—not very efficient.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.84,0:34:58.61,Default,,0,0,0,,If the four congregations were redistributed \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.61,0:35:00.62,Default,,0,0,0,,into three congregations, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.62,0:35:03.35,Default,,0,0,0,,average meeting attendance \Nfor each congregation \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.35,0:35:06.45,Default,,0,0,0,,would increase \Nto about 160 per meeting, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.45,0:35:09.16,Default,,0,0,0,,while still fitting comfortably \Nin that Kingdom Hall. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.16,0:35:12.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And this would now allow \Nfor an open slot in the schedule, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.76,0:35:15.53,Default,,0,0,0,,which could be used \Nto meet needs in the area \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.53,0:35:18.70,Default,,0,0,0,,without requiring new construction.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.70,0:35:22.07,Default,,0,0,0,,In the first three years of the LDC program, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.07,0:35:24.94,Default,,0,0,0,,fully utilizing our existing facilities \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.94,0:35:28.44,Default,,0,0,0,,played a part in reducing \Nthe backlog of Kingdom Hall projects \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.44,0:35:32.05,Default,,0,0,0,,from 14,000 to approximately 10,000. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.05,0:35:34.62,Default,,0,0,0,,This saved millions of dollars. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.62,0:35:37.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, this does not meet every need, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.39,0:35:39.49,Default,,0,0,0,,and there is still a significant need \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.49,0:35:41.12,Default,,0,0,0,,to construct new Kingdom Halls \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.12,0:35:44.76,Default,,0,0,0,,to provide suitable places of worship.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.76,0:35:46.76,Default,,0,0,0,,How does the branch office \Nmake these decisions, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.76,0:35:50.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and how are priorities set? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.13,0:35:52.13,Default,,0,0,0,,All options are examined \Nas the Branch Committees \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.13,0:35:54.14,Default,,0,0,0,,work with their Local Design/Construction \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.14,0:35:56.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and Service departments. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.14,0:35:58.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Transportation needs\N—such as distance, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.97,0:36:01.01,Default,,0,0,0,,opportunities for carpooling, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.01,0:36:03.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and availability \Nof public transportation—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.24,0:36:06.75,Default,,0,0,0,,are taken into account. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.75,0:36:09.25,Default,,0,0,0,,In many cases, \Ncongregations can be sized \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.25,0:36:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,to make better use of available seats \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.32,0:36:14.32,Default,,0,0,0,,in Kingdom Halls \Nthat have already been built. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.32,0:36:16.59,Default,,0,0,0,,However, \Nwhen they are needed, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.59,0:36:20.53,Default,,0,0,0,,new Kingdom Halls can be constructed \Nusing simple, standard designs \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.53,0:36:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,that make wise use of donated funds.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.07,0:36:28.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, all of this must be done \Nwith the big picture in mind. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.34,0:36:30.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It is the spiritual needs \Nof the congregations \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.87,0:36:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,that are of the utmost priority. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.88,0:36:37.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The structures themselves are not \Nthe focus of these centers of pure worship, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.88,0:36:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,but rather it is the people \Nwho use the facilities.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.15,0:36:45.82,Default,,0,0,0,,On one occasion, \Nas they passed the temple, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.82,0:36:48.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Mark 13:1 quotes one of Jesus’ disciples \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.69,0:36:50.99,Default,,0,0,0,,admiring the structure when he said: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.99,0:36:55.16,Default,,0,0,0,,“Teacher, see! \Nwhat wonderful stones and buildings!” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.16,0:36:56.46,Default,,0,0,0,,However, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.46,0:36:58.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus’ reply simply indicated \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.73,0:37:02.07,Default,,0,0,0,,that the building itself would not last. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.07,0:37:06.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It was people Jesus was concerned with.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.04,0:37:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Likewise, \Nthe Kingdom Halls that we build today \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.04,0:37:12.05,Default,,0,0,0,,will not last forever. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.05,0:37:14.78,Default,,0,0,0,,But these centers of pure worship \Nbring people together \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.78,0:37:18.09,Default,,0,0,0,,so that we can serve Jehovah \Nas a united group\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.09,0:37:22.52,Default,,0,0,0,,—and that will last forever.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.52,0:37:24.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether we assist in the construction \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.16,0:37:27.53,Default,,0,0,0,,of the many Kingdom Halls \Nthat are still needed \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.53,0:37:30.03,Default,,0,0,0,,or help to renovate and maintain \Nexisting Kingdom Halls, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.03,0:37:32.77,Default,,0,0,0,,it is our shared privilege \Nto help provide \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.77,0:37:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,suitable meeting places \Nfor our brothers and sisters. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.54,0:37:38.54,Default,,0,0,0,,In this way, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.54,0:37:40.94,Default,,0,0,0,,we each support \N“the faithful and discreet slave” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.94,0:37:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,as they provide what is needed \Nso that each congregation \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.55,0:37:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,can praise Jehovah \Nin a suitable place of worship.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.92,0:37:54.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Thomas Kalimeris, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.92,0:37:56.99,Default,,0,0,0,,who serves at the United States branch, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.99,0:37:58.99,Default,,0,0,0,,together with his wife, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.99,0:38:02.76,Default,,0,0,0,,has spent close to four decades \Nsupporting various aspects \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.76,0:38:05.87,Default,,0,0,0,,of the organization’s construction projects. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.87,0:38:08.37,Default,,0,0,0,,What has that experience taught him? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.37,0:38:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That the work is not run by us.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.14,0:38:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Throughout history, men have built \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.15,0:38:21.88,Default,,0,0,0,,many beautiful and impressive buildings. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.88,0:38:24.39,Default,,0,0,0,,These structures \Nhave usually brought glory to men, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.39,0:38:26.39,Default,,0,0,0,,not to God. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.39,0:38:28.39,Default,,0,0,0,,But those men are long gone, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.39,0:38:32.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and even many of the structures \Nno longer exist. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.76,0:38:36.83,Default,,0,0,0,,How true is the scripture at Psalm 127:1: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.83,0:38:39.80,Default,,0,0,0,,“Unless Jehovah builds the house, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.80,0:38:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,it is in vain \Nthat its builders work hard on it.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.44,0:38:49.11,Default,,0,0,0,,In our time too, \NJehovah is using his people to build. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.11,0:38:52.91,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re working hard \Nto build spirituality in interested ones, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.91,0:38:54.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and also we build structures \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.92,0:38:58.19,Default,,0,0,0,,in order to help individuals to learn \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.19,0:39:00.76,Default,,0,0,0,,about Jehovah and serve him. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.76,0:39:03.59,Default,,0,0,0,,In this type of construction\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.59,0:39:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,—both spiritual and physical construction—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.59,0:39:07.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve been involved for most of my life.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.60,0:39:10.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I was born in Greece. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.06,0:39:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Our family came into contact \Nwith the truth in the early sixties. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.80,0:39:17.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I was baptized when I was in high school. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.77,0:39:22.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I left school to get \Nsome practical training in architecture, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.41,0:39:25.11,Default,,0,0,0,,but I made pioneering my career. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.11,0:39:28.68,Default,,0,0,0,,In 1973, \NI married my dear wife, Margaret, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.68,0:39:31.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and together \Nwe enjoyed many assignments. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.32,0:39:33.59,Default,,0,0,0,,We pioneered\N—special pioneering. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.59,0:39:36.76,Default,,0,0,0,,We went to Gilead. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.76,0:39:38.83,Default,,0,0,0,,We were invited to Bethel \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.83,0:39:42.63,Default,,0,0,0,,in 1979 to work \Nin the Engineering Department. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.63,0:39:46.33,Default,,0,0,0,,We worked on designing new branches, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.33,0:39:49.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Assembly Halls, Kingdom Halls, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.24,0:39:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,renovation of existing branches \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.44,0:39:56.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and remote translation offices. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.91,0:40:01.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Before we came to Bethel, we had seen how \NJehovah provided for us individually. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.38,0:40:03.95,Default,,0,0,0,,But now we had the opportunity \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.95,0:40:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to see how Jehovah provided \Nfor the needs of his organization globally.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.42,0:40:14.56,Default,,0,0,0,,By the year 2000, \Nit became apparent that the present facility \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.56,0:40:19.33,Default,,0,0,0,,of the Britain branch \Nwas not meeting their needs. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.33,0:40:21.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So a site was located \N50 miles (80 km) north of London \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.47,0:40:24.41,Default,,0,0,0,,to relocate the branch there. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.41,0:40:26.41,Default,,0,0,0,,However, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.41,0:40:29.48,Default,,0,0,0,,the Governing Body \Ndecided to cancel the project. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.48,0:40:31.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So in 2008, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.48,0:40:34.92,Default,,0,0,0,,the Governing Body wrote \Nthat now is the time\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.92,0:40:37.99,Default,,0,0,0,,—Jehovah’s time—\Nto find property \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.99,0:40:39.99,Default,,0,0,0,,closer to London. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.99,0:40:42.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So a project team was formed, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:42.12,0:40:44.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and a few years went by,\Nand a number of properties were searched,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.83,0:40:48.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and one was located closer to London. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.06,0:40:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,If something we plan falls through, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.00,0:40:53.97,Default,,0,0,0,,it could mean \Nthat Jehovah has something else\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.97,0:40:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,—or better— in mind to meet \Nthe needs of his organization.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.61,0:41:02.74,Default,,0,0,0,,While working in the Haiti branch, \Nwe learned a lesson: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.74,0:41:06.55,Default,,0,0,0,,not to compromise on safety. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.55,0:41:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The Brooklyn Engineering Department \Ndid the drawings for the branch, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.72,0:41:13.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and a local contractor was hired \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.85,0:41:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,to build the structural work. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.86,0:41:17.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the contractor, \Nwhen he reviewed the drawings, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.73,0:41:21.23,Default,,0,0,0,,told the Branch Committee: \N“Really, this is overdesigned. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.23,0:41:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re wasting a lot of money \Nby putting all the steel in the building.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.60,0:41:30.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So we wrote back and said: \N“No, the drawings are OK. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.10,0:41:33.34,Default,,0,0,0,,“The branch is designed \Naccording to the seismic zone that it’s in. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.34,0:41:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And the contractor is to go ahead \Nwith the plans as drawn.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:38.05,0:41:42.65,Default,,0,0,0,,In 2010, \Nwhen the earthquake came to Haiti, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.65,0:41:46.22,Default,,0,0,0,,hundreds of thousands of people died \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.22,0:41:50.26,Default,,0,0,0,,because of inferior materials \Nand methods of construction. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.26,0:41:52.29,Default,,0,0,0,,However, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.29,0:41:54.86,Default,,0,0,0,,the branch did not suffer any damage, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.86,0:41:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and many people went there to find refuge. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.73,0:42:02.44,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re so glad that Jehovah did not allow us \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.44,0:42:05.24,Default,,0,0,0,,to be swayed in this case.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.24,0:42:09.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah continues to direct \Na great physical building work \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.68,0:42:11.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and a spiritual work. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.65,0:42:14.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah trains his people \Nhow to work together \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.42,0:42:16.45,Default,,0,0,0,,for the work just ahead of us\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.45,0:42:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,—the beautification of this earth \Nto a paradise. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.19,0:42:24.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It is so important that we \N‘trust in Jehovah \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.76,0:42:28.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and not to lean \Nupon our own understanding.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.53,0:42:30.76,Default,,0,0,0,,A life of building with Jehovah\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.76,0:42:34.13,Default,,0,0,0,,has shown me the wisdom of Psalm 127:1.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.13,0:42:37.40,Default,,0,0,0,,If we keep building our lives with Jehovah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.40,0:42:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,our building work will never be in vain.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:45.08,0:42:48.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The more responsibility a brother \Nis given in the organization, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:48.22,0:42:50.99,Default,,0,0,0,,the less he feels he is in control. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.99,0:42:55.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, he will clearly see how Jehovah \Ntakes the lead in the organization. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.82,0:42:59.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And Brother Kalimeris’ experience \Nconfirms that. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.39,0:43:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The account about how the branch in Haiti \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.86,0:43:04.20,Default,,0,0,0,,was protected from earthquake damage \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.20,0:43:06.87,Default,,0,0,0,,sent chills down my spine. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.87,0:43:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,While some buildings looked like this, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.24,0:43:12.71,Default,,0,0,0,,our branch looked like this. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.71,0:43:16.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And it wasn’t the ingenuity of the brothers \N that protected the branch, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.81,0:43:19.88,Default,,0,0,0,,but wisdom that only Jehovah can provide. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.88,0:43:23.95,Default,,0,0,0,,But how can we apply \Nthat same wisdom in our lives? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.95,0:43:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s consider three ways we can do so.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.50,0:43:36.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah has warned us that we’re living \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.60,0:43:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,in “critical times hard to deal with.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.77,0:43:45.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And Jesus foretold that in the last days \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.97,0:43:49.04,Default,,0,0,0,,there would be great “earthquakes \Nin one place after another” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.04,0:43:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and other “fearful sights.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.98,0:43:57.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Many of us either have or will be affected \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:57.89,0:44:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,by some form of natural disaster.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:04.02,0:44:08.60,Default,,0,0,0,,If this happens, how can we be prepared?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:08.60,0:44:10.03,Default,,0,0,0,,First, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:10.03,0:44:13.10,Default,,0,0,0,,we can prepare spiritually by maintaining \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:13.10,0:44:15.97,Default,,0,0,0,,a close relationship with Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:15.97,0:44:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,He is “the God of all comfort,” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.84,0:44:22.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and he can comfort us \Nin times of tribulation. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.04,0:44:24.51,Default,,0,0,0,,How does he do this?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.51,0:44:27.72,Default,,0,0,0,,We do not expect divine intervention. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:27.72,0:44:30.95,Default,,0,0,0,,But if we pray during times of distress, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:30.95,0:44:34.29,Default,,0,0,0,,his powerful holy spirit \Ncan bring Bible passages \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:34.29,0:44:38.29,Default,,0,0,0,,back to mind to comfort us.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.29,0:44:40.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Second, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:40.29,0:44:43.23,Default,,0,0,0,,we can take practical steps, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:43.23,0:44:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,perhaps preparing an emergency kit. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:46.40,0:44:51.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Our kit could contain \Nthe following items if possible: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.24,0:44:53.77,Default,,0,0,0,,first-aid supplies, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:53.77,0:44:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,bottled water, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:55.84,0:44:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and nonperishable food.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:01.28,0:45:04.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, we shouldn’t forget \Nto update the elders \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.52,0:45:08.06,Default,,0,0,0,,with our latest contact information. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.06,0:45:10.06,Default,,0,0,0,,If we don’t do so, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:10.06,0:45:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,valuable time could be lost in a disaster.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:17.10,0:45:20.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Additionally, \Nduring a Family Worship evening, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:20.87,0:45:24.74,Default,,0,0,0,,our family could review \Nthe types of disasters that might happen \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:24.74,0:45:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and what could be done in each situation\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.24,0:45:31.41,Default,,0,0,0,,—such as where we meet, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.41,0:45:35.72,Default,,0,0,0,,how we contact the elders, and so forth.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.72,0:45:37.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And third, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.72,0:45:40.79,Default,,0,0,0,,we can help others \Nwhen they’re experiencing a disaster, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:40.79,0:45:44.06,Default,,0,0,0,,knowing they’d do the same for us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:44.06,0:45:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,How can we do this? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:48.70,0:45:52.73,Default,,0,0,0,,By offering prayers in their behalf, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:52.73,0:45:57.07,Default,,0,0,0,,by volunteering to assist \Nwith disaster relief efforts, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.07,0:46:02.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and by contributing donations \Nto the worldwide work.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:02.91,0:46:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,No, we can’t avoid all natural disasters. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:09.02,0:46:11.45,Default,,0,0,0,,But if we prepare spiritually, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.45,0:46:13.45,Default,,0,0,0,,practically, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.45,0:46:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and help others currently affected, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:15.59,0:46:17.93,Default,,0,0,0,,we can take comfort in knowing \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.93,0:46:19.99,Default,,0,0,0,,that in Jehovah’s eyes \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.99,0:46:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,we are prepared.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.80,0:46:26.63,Default,,0,0,0,,That was great, practical advice \Nfor all of us to take to heart. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:26.63,0:46:30.50,Default,,0,0,0,,But there are some things \Nwe can do to help our local congregation. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.50,0:46:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s turn briefly \Nto interview Brother Bram Siegel, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:34.24,0:46:37.34,Default,,0,0,0,,who’s with \Nthe Coordinators’ Committee Office.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:37.34,0:46:39.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Bram, how can all of us cooperate \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:39.95,0:46:42.05,Default,,0,0,0,,with the congregation arrangement \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:42.05,0:46:44.32,Default,,0,0,0,,when a disaster hits?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:44.32,0:46:47.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Immediately after a disaster occurs, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:47.29,0:46:49.29,Default,,0,0,0,,each field service group overseer \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:49.29,0:46:51.29,Default,,0,0,0,,will contact everyone in his group \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.29,0:46:53.29,Default,,0,0,0,,to make sure that all are accounted for \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.29,0:46:56.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and to see if anyone needs assistance. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.60,0:46:58.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So each of us \Nshould make sure to give the elders \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:58.70,0:47:01.24,Default,,0,0,0,,our up-to-date contact information. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:01.24,0:47:04.27,Default,,0,0,0,,That way they can reach us \Nwhen something happens.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.27,0:47:08.41,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s a very important reminder\N—good point! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:08.41,0:47:11.65,Default,,0,0,0,,But what if my area \Nwas not hit by the disaster \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:11.65,0:47:14.08,Default,,0,0,0,,but an adjacent town or city was? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:14.08,0:47:16.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Can I just travel there on my own to help, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.15,0:47:18.75,Default,,0,0,0,,or what should I do?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:18.75,0:47:22.62,Default,,0,0,0,,We really appreciate \Nthe beautiful spirit the brotherhood shows \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.62,0:47:25.23,Default,,0,0,0,,when it comes to providing disaster relief. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:25.23,0:47:28.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Really, the best time \Nto make yourself available to help \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:28.60,0:47:30.26,Default,,0,0,0,,is right now, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:30.26,0:47:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,before a disaster occurs. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:32.40,0:47:35.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Just ask your local elders \Nfor an application. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:35.17,0:47:38.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Later, when there’s a need \Nto provide disaster relief, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:38.01,0:47:42.14,Default,,0,0,0,,the branch office will know \Nthat you’re willing and ready to assist.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.14,0:47:45.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much, Bram, \Nfor those important reminders.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:45.98,0:47:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:50.08,0:47:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,When large disasters occur, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:52.32,0:47:55.02,Default,,0,0,0,,our brothers and sisters \Nmay have to relocate\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:55.02,0:47:56.99,Default,,0,0,0,,—perhaps even to another country. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:56.99,0:48:00.63,Default,,0,0,0,,As refugees, they face unique challenges. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:00.63,0:48:04.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You will notice that the Watchtower study \Nfor the week of July 3 \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:04.73,0:48:06.83,Default,,0,0,0,,provides practical suggestions \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.83,0:48:10.27,Default,,0,0,0,,on how we can support \Nsuch brothers and sisters.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:10.27,0:48:12.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And I’m sure you agree \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:12.34,0:48:15.54,Default,,0,0,0,,that the guidance \NJehovah’s organization provides, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:15.54,0:48:19.81,Default,,0,0,0,,the love and care that we experience \Nevery day as a people for his name, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:19.81,0:48:22.62,Default,,0,0,0,,the spiritual paradise that we dwell in\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:22.62,0:48:26.65,Default,,0,0,0,,—all of that makes us want \Nto praise our heavenly Father. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:26.65,0:48:31.39,Default,,0,0,0,,This brings us to this month’s \Nmusic video which is entitled \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:31.39,0:48:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We Marvel at Your Work.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:41.94,0:48:50.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The work of the Kingdom,\Nin my lifetime and before,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:50.01,0:48:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Provides me with your written Word, \Nthe truth, and so much more.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:58.72,0:49:06.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Your faithful slave, discreet and wise, \Nprovides increasing light\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:06.89,0:49:17.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And sends out men who shepherd me \Nwith loving oversight.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:17.34,0:49:25.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I know expectations \Nat conventions will be met.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:25.15,0:49:33.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And afterward, I always say,\N“Now that’s the best one yet!”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:33.49,0:49:41.90,Default,,0,0,0,,At weekly meetings, \NI can feel your thoughtful, loving care\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.90,0:49:52.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And learn how best to preach and teach \Nand have a fuller share.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:52.57,0:50:08.86,Default,,0,0,0,,We marvel at your work\NAnd what the Kingdom’s done so far.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.86,0:50:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We cherish Kingdom rule.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:17.10,0:50:25.54,Default,,0,0,0,,We grow in faith to realize \Nthe kind of God you are.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:25.54,0:50:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We look ahead to blessings \Nthat your Kingdom soon will bring.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:42.46,0:50:50.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You give us the honor \Nto be workers on your side,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:50.13,0:50:58.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Our ministry that lets us show \Nthe love we feel inside.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:58.47,0:51:06.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The depth of understanding \Nand the peace of mind you give,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:06.65,0:51:16.82,Default,,0,0,0,,They teach us what is pure and true; \Nthey show the way to live.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:16.82,0:51:25.37,Default,,0,0,0,,The songs that express \Nwhat’s in my heart so very well\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:25.37,0:51:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And Fam’ly Worship ev’nings \Ngive your spirit room to dwell.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:33.44,0:51:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Our unity, despite whatever language \Nwe might speak,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:42.32,0:51:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Proves that our loving brotherhood \Nin this world is unique.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:52.39,0:52:08.84,Default,,0,0,0,,We marvel at your work\NAnd what the Kingdom’s done so far.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:08.84,0:52:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We cherish Kingdom rule.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:17.22,0:52:25.33,Default,,0,0,0,,We grow in faith \Nto realize the kind of God you are.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:25.33,0:52:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We look ahead to blessings \Nthat your Kingdom soon will bring.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:46.78,0:52:48.62,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s beautiful. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:48.62,0:52:50.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And how can we show our appreciation \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:50.82,0:52:54.12,Default,,0,0,0,,for Jehovah’s provisions in a practical way? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:54.12,0:52:58.26,Default,,0,0,0,,By taking seriously \Nour God-given assignment to preach. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:58.26,0:53:00.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And we have seen developments \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:00.26,0:53:02.83,Default,,0,0,0,,in our preaching methods \Nin the past few years.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:02.83,0:53:07.43,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, in 2001, \Nwith the Governing Body’s approval, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:07.43,0:53:10.84,Default,,0,0,0,,our brothers in France \Nstarted using a variety of methods\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:10.84,0:53:15.18,Default,,0,0,0,, to carry out our public witnessing, \Nincluding the use of carts. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:15.18,0:53:18.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The trial resulted \Nin many good experiences. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:18.61,0:53:21.82,Default,,0,0,0,,As a result, in 2011, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:21.82,0:53:24.25,Default,,0,0,0,,a pilot project with cart witnessing \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:24.25,0:53:28.72,Default,,0,0,0,,in New York City, U.S.A., was approved.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:28.72,0:53:31.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Since Manhattan, in New York City, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:31.19,0:53:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,had a ratio of 1 Jehovah’s Witness\Nto 657 inhabitants, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:35.36,0:53:37.50,Default,,0,0,0,,this was a perfect choice. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:37.50,0:53:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That was the beginning \Nof a pilot program in Manhattan. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:42.87,0:53:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The program lasted one year, \Nusing many graduates \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:46.07,0:53:49.51,Default,,0,0,0,,from what was then \Nthe Bible School for Christian Couples.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:49.51,0:53:51.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Although different tables \Nwere used at the time, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:51.88,0:53:53.88,Default,,0,0,0,,it was evident that a mobile cart \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:53.88,0:53:55.98,Default,,0,0,0,,had many advantages. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:55.98,0:53:58.82,Default,,0,0,0,,As a result, today, \NJehovah’s Witnesses are well-known \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:58.82,0:54:01.72,Default,,0,0,0,,for their public witnessing using carts  \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:01.72,0:54:03.49,Default,,0,0,0,,designed to display their literature. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:03.49,0:54:04.89,Default,,0,0,0,,By means of this method, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:04.89,0:54:08.13,Default,,0,0,0,,good news from the Bible \Ncan be taken to many places \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:08.13,0:54:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and easily becomes available \Nto countless people.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:13.43,0:54:16.67,Default,,0,0,0,,These carts include different posters that: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:16.67,0:54:19.67,Default,,0,0,0,,call attention \Nto our well-known publications, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:19.67,0:54:23.31,Default,,0,0,0,,invite people to accept \Nfree home Bible studies, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:23.31,0:54:27.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and direct passersby to our official website. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:27.35,0:54:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Here are just a few examples of how \Nthis method has had many good results.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:33.55,0:54:35.56,Default,,0,0,0,,My name is Mi Jung You. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:35.56,0:54:38.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The first time I met Jehovah’s Witnesses \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:38.12,0:54:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,was more than 20 years ago. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:39.76,0:54:42.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I started studying \Nin the You Can Live Forever book, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:42.86,0:54:44.93,Default,,0,0,0,,but about a month later, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:44.93,0:54:46.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I had to stop studying. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:46.93,0:54:50.17,Default,,0,0,0,,After that, \NI would accept the magazines, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:50.17,0:54:52.51,Default,,0,0,0,,but I never ended up \Nstudying the Bible again.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:52.51,0:54:55.51,Default,,0,0,0,,In June of 2014, though, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:55.51,0:54:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I saw the public witnessing stand. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:57.84,0:55:01.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I realized that it belonged \Nto Jehovah’s Witnesses. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:01.08,0:55:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So many of the different publications \Nthey had caught my eye. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:04.72,0:55:09.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So I asked if it would be OK \Nif I took a copy of each one. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:09.32,0:55:11.46,Default,,0,0,0,,We ended up exchanging numbers, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:11.46,0:55:14.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and a few weeks later \Nthe brother contacted me. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:14.36,0:55:18.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I began studying \Nthe Bible again with the couple \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:18.50,0:55:23.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and one month later \Nstarted attending meetings regularly.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:23.34,0:55:26.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I was baptized in October of 2015 \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:26.81,0:55:30.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and started auxiliary pioneering \Nright away for ten months. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:30.51,0:55:32.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I’m serving as a regular pioneer. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:32.75,0:55:36.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Public witnessing helped me find the truth, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:36.45,0:55:40.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and it’s a way for me to meet people \Nthat are interested like I was. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:40.62,0:55:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I have really come to cherish \Nthe public witnessing work.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:46.09,0:55:49.06,Default,,0,0,0,,My name is Jacob Salomé. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:49.06,0:55:51.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I work as a driver and spent most of my life \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:51.40,0:55:53.53,Default,,0,0,0,,traveling all over Peru. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:53.53,0:55:57.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of this, I had problems \Nwith the woman I was living with. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:57.94,0:56:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I never spent time at home \Nand practically lived in the truck.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:05.95,0:56:08.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I would see Jehovah’s Witnesses preaching \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:08.35,0:56:10.38,Default,,0,0,0,,on the streets near the buses. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:10.38,0:56:12.79,Default,,0,0,0,,But since I was always driving, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:12.79,0:56:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn’t park or even talk to them. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:16.52,0:56:20.26,Default,,0,0,0,,But once, I saw some Witnesses \Npreaching in a public square. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:20.26,0:56:22.33,Default,,0,0,0,,So I went up to them to ask them \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:22.33,0:56:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,what the Bible says about family matters.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:27.40,0:56:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,This marked a change in my life. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:32.07,0:56:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,My girlfriend and I \Nbegan attending meetings, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:36.74,0:56:40.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and then we got married and got baptized. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:40.78,0:56:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we are Jehovah’s Witnesses.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:45.59,0:56:50.26,Default,,0,0,0,,As Annies and I were standing by our cart, \Nwe met young Sudharshan. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:50.26,0:56:54.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Annies showed him our tract \NCan the Dead Really Live Again? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:54.26,0:56:57.06,Default,,0,0,0,,He was surprised and said, \N“How is it possible?” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:57.06,0:57:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,When she explained to him Acts 24:15, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:00.00,0:57:04.50,Default,,0,0,0,,he exclaimed: “I am a Christian. \NI never knew this!” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:04.50,0:57:06.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I asked him, \N“Would you like to learn more \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:06.87,0:57:09.18,Default,,0,0,0,,about such wonderful things \Nfrom the Bible?” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:09.18,0:57:12.58,Default,,0,0,0,,He asked, \N“Can you tell me right now?” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:12.58,0:57:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,There and then, I discussed the first chapter \Nof the Bible Teach book. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:15.92,0:57:18.08,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s how it started.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:18.08,0:57:20.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Sudharshan brought his friend, Sagar. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:20.52,0:57:24.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Sagar, in turn, \Nbrought Shiva and Srikanth along. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:24.56,0:57:27.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Three of them are attending \Nour meetings regularly. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:27.03,0:57:29.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Sagar even turned down a job offer \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:29.70,0:57:32.87,Default,,0,0,0,,that conflicted with Bible principles. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:32.87,0:57:35.94,Default,,0,0,0,,One tract resulted in many Bible studies. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:35.94,0:57:38.10,Default,,0,0,0,,We can really see Jehovah’s blessing \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:38.10,0:57:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,on this form of public witnessing.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:55.49,0:57:58.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Without a doubt, \Ncart witnessing is being used \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:58.29,0:58:00.66,Default,,0,0,0,,to help preach \Nthe good news of God’s Kingdom \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:00.66,0:58:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“in all the inhabited earth \Nfor a witness to all the nations.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:19.68,0:58:22.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The examples we’ve seen in this program \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:22.58,0:58:25.32,Default,,0,0,0,,truly highlight how Jehovah and Jesus \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:25.32,0:58:29.59,Default,,0,0,0,,use all of us to get \Nan unprecedented work accomplished.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:29.59,0:58:32.49,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ve seen how young brothers are trained \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:32.49,0:58:34.89,Default,,0,0,0,,to take the lead in the congregations, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:34.89,0:58:37.13,Default,,0,0,0,,how videos are produced \Naround the world \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:37.13,0:58:39.03,Default,,0,0,0,,for our spiritual benefit, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:39.03,0:58:43.30,Default,,0,0,0,,the work that goes into better \Nutilizing our Kingdom Halls, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:43.30,0:58:46.57,Default,,0,0,0,,how wisdom from Jehovah \Nbenefits our construction work, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:46.57,0:58:51.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and how appropriate it is to praise \Nour heavenly Father for all his works. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:51.54,0:58:53.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And last, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:53.38,0:58:56.98,Default,,0,0,0,,we were encouraged to continue \Nin our public witnessing efforts \N
Dialogue: 0,0:58:56.98,0:59:00.02,Default,,0,0,0,,as we clearly see Jehovah’s blessing. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:00.02,0:59:04.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, we are proud \Nto be Jehovah’s Witnesses. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:04.46,0:59:08.36,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the best organization on earth.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:08.36,0:59:10.10,Default,,0,0,0,,To conclude, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:10.10,0:59:14.03,Default,,0,0,0,,we’d like to share \Nthis postcard from Iceland. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:14.03,0:59:17.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Almost 335,000 people live \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:17.10,0:59:19.67,Default,,0,0,0,,on this North Atlantic island nation, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:19.67,0:59:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,of which about 380 are Jehovah’s Witnesses.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:24.51,0:59:27.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Iceland is known \Nfor being the land of ice and fire, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:27.48,0:59:30.72,Default,,0,0,0,,as it has both a lot of volcanic activity \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:30.72,0:59:33.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and Europe’s largest glacier. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:33.29,0:59:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,In their free time, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:35.12,0:59:38.49,Default,,0,0,0,,the Witnesses in Iceland \Nenjoy hiking in the beautiful nature\N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:38.49,0:59:42.93,Default,,0,0,0,, or riding on horseback \Non Icelandic horses.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:42.93,0:59:46.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The preaching work  \Nin Iceland began in 1929. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:46.77,0:59:51.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Lindal was the only publisher \Non the island for nearly 18 years. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:51.64,0:59:54.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, the 380 publishers conduct \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:54.54,0:59:58.01,Default,,0,0,0,,approximately 270 Bible studies, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:58.01,0:59:59.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and almost 700 people\N
Dialogue: 0,0:59:59.91,1:00:04.62,Default,,0,0,0,,attended the Memorial of Christ’s death \Nlast year.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:04.62,1:00:07.82,Default,,0,0,0,,In the winter, \Nthe sun is up for only a few hours. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:07.82,1:00:11.09,Default,,0,0,0,,While the Witnesses \Nuse the limited sunlight wisely\N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:11.09,1:00:13.89,Default,,0,0,0,,—going from door to door \Nor business witnessing—\N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:13.89,1:00:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,they are not scared by the darkness. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:18.03,1:00:21.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Some congregations use tiny lights \Non their public witnessing carts \N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:21.83,1:00:25.34,Default,,0,0,0,,so that the passersby will see the carts.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:25.34,1:00:28.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, the weather in Iceland \Ncan change quickly. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:28.61,1:00:33.15,Default,,0,0,0,,To prevent literature from being damaged \Nby rain or other weather elements, \N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:33.15,1:00:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,some congregations use plastic covers \Non the literature.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:37.92,1:00:40.65,Default,,0,0,0,,In 2011, a Polish group was established \N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:40.65,1:00:42.79,Default,,0,0,0,,in the capital city of Reykjavik, \N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:42.79,1:00:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and in 2016, a congregation \Nwith over 40 publishers was formed. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:48.93,1:00:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, they conduct over 20 Bible studies.\N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:53.47,1:00:56.77,Default,,0,0,0,,All the brothers and sisters in Iceland \Nsend their warm Christian love. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:00:56.77,1:01:00.14,Default,,0,0,0,,We pray that Jehovah will continue \N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:00.14,1:01:03.68,Default,,0,0,0,,to bless their efforts in praising his name. \N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:03.68,1:01:05.71,Default,,0,0,0,,This is JW Broadcasting \N
Dialogue: 0,1:01:05.71,1:01:08.47,Default,,0,0,0,,from the world headquarters \Nof Jehovah’s Witnesses.\N
